The paper proposes a method for image retrieval based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and focuses on extracting discriminative representations containing regional information of small objects. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses adversarial techniques and proposes a novel method for soft region proposal, which could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its method on standard image retrieval datasets, indicating that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to generate semantic maps, which could also place it in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
